---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Hero from "../components/hero.astro";
import {Image} from "astro:assets";
---

<Layout title="Welcome to Astro.">
  <main class="max-w-[1440px] mx-auto px-[50px] mt-[30px]">
    <Hero class="mb-[180px]" />
    <div class="flex items-start mb-[100px]">
      <h2 class="sticky top-5 text-[28px] font-medium leading-[1.2] lg:w-[430px] text-gray-800">Inbox & Scheduling</h2>
      <div class="space-y-8">
        <p class="leading-[1.4] text-gray-700 text-[24px] max-w-[660px]">
          Unlike in other todolists your can’t just type task and immediately complete it. First you have to add it in your inbox
        </p>
        <Image src="/screenshots/inbox-crud.gif" alt="inbox" width="880" height="680" />
        <p class="leading-[1.4] text-gray-700 text-[24px] max-w-[660px]">
          Only after you plan you inbox-task in `Plan` tab your can mark it as complete
        </p>
        <Image src="/screenshots/inbox-planning.gif" alt="inbox" width="880" height="680" />
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex items-start mb-[100px]">
      <h2 class="sticky top-5 text-[28px] font-medium leading-[1.2] lg:w-[430px] text-gray-800">No labels, priorities</h2>
      <div class="space-y-8">
        <p class="leading-[1.4] text-gray-700 text-[24px] max-w-[660px]">
          Priorities add extra layer to your mental model of task management. Instead we suggest just use ordering
        </p>
        <Image src="/screenshots/inbox-crud.gif" alt="inbox" width="880" height="680" />
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex items-start mb-[100px]">
      <h2 class="sticky top-5 text-[28px] font-medium leading-[1.2] lg:w-[430px] text-gray-800">Blazing-ly fast offline first updates</h2>
      <div class="space-y-8">
        <p class="leading-[1.4] text-gray-700 text-[24px] max-w-[660px]">
          After you done something we store this action locally, and they sync it with server. If you left app after making some update and sync not happened: don’t worry we will sync this update on your next app opening
        </p>
        <Image src="/screenshots/blazingly.gif" alt="inbox" width="880" height="680" />
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex items-start mb-[100px]">
      <h2 class="sticky top-5 text-[28px] font-medium leading-[1.2] lg:w-[430px] text-gray-800">Use your tasks from linear</h2>
      <div class="space-y-8">
        <p class="leading-[1.4] text-gray-700 text-[24px] max-w-[660px]">
          If you are working in company that uses project management tool you can import your tasks from this tool into your inbox.
        </p>
        <Image src="/screenshots/linear-integration.gif" alt="inbox" width="880" height="680" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
